        "en": "The Trial: Salih (AS) was sent to the people of Thamud, who built palaces in the mountains and possessed power, but they fell into the trap of arrogance. Salih's trial was facing a people who asked for an impossible sign; when Allah responded and the she-camel emerged from the rock, instead of prostrating, they grew more tyrannical. The trial was reconciling the guidance of a rebellious people with preserving the mission in the face of 9 men who spread corruption. Every time they saw the sign, they tried to bury it, eventually planning to kill the she-camel and then Prophet Salih, thinking they would end the call.\n\nPatience and Certainty: Salih patiently endured his people's mockery and vile conspiracies. He did not falter at their threats, but reminded them of Allah's right, warning them against killing the camel. His certainty in Allah was unshakable; while they planned evil, he was reassured by his Lord's promise. He faced their arrogance with strange steadfastness, realizing the Prophet's role is to convey the message, and Allah is the Guardian of the truth. He endured their denial and accusations of witchcraft, counting all of it for the sake of Allah who chose him for this difficult task.\n\nThe Divine Gift: The Divine Verdict arrived to end this obstinacy; after they killed the camel, Allah gave them three days, then the 'Blast' came and destroyed them all. At that moment, the gift was the salvation of Salih and the believers by Allah's mercy, emerging from the ruins in peace. Salih left behind an impact that time cannot erase, a witness that miracles are not for amusement, and whoever challenges Allah finds a dire end, while whoever follows the truth finds salvation in this life and the next, regardless of his enemies' power."
